radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild hypoventilatory changes at the dependent portions of the lung bases. No focal consolidation or effusion. The cecum has circular calcifications consistent with appendicoliths, a fluid-filled tubular rim enhancing structure distal to this region, and focal cecal wall thickening surrounding the appendiceal base. No surrounding fluid collections detected. A small cyst within the left adnexa measuring 1.9 x 1.8 cm. Small amount of free pelvic fluid. No worrisome lytic or sclerotic lesions detected.
